00:18:58.205 --> 00:19:00.440 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>there'll be</i>
 <i>no penalty kicks.</i>

00:19:00.474 --> 00:19:03.645 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>After a ten minute break,</i>
 <i>we'll start with extra time.</i>

00:19:03.678 --> 00:19:05.046 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>Five minutes</i>
 <i>for the first half</i>

00:19:05.079 --> 00:19:07.280 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>and five minutes</i>
 <i>for the second half.</i>

00:19:08.482 --> 00:19:11.052 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>If neither team can score</i>
 <i>within that time limit,</i>

00:19:11.085 --> 00:19:12.386 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>there'll be no other choice</i>

00:19:12.419 --> 00:19:14.889 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>but to declare both teams</i>
 <i>the winners.</i>

00:19:14.922 --> 00:19:19.192 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>This is a rule implemented</i>
 <i>for the youth tournament.</i>

00:19:19.226 --> 00:19:21.228 position:16% line:83% align:start
So they tied the match,
after all.

00:19:21.261 --> 00:19:22.530 position:19% line:89% align:start
We're so sorry, Coach.

00:19:22.563 --> 00:19:24.098 position:16% line:83% align:start
If you gave it your all
out there,

00:19:24.132 --> 00:19:25.198 position:24% line:83% align:start
then you shouldn't
apologize.

00:19:25.232 --> 00:19:26.500 position:10% line:89% align:start
But if you didn't do that...

00:19:26.534 --> 00:19:28.569 position:13% line:83% align:start
then I can't forgive you,
after all.

00:19:28.603 --> 00:19:29.504 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-Huh?

00:19:29.537 --> 00:19:32.372 position:21% line:83% align:start
Soccer is like that.
It's unpredictable.

00:19:32.406 --> 00:19:33.473 position:19% line:89% align:start
That's why we have to

00:19:33.508 --> 00:19:35.208 position:13% line:83% align:start
take advantage of the lead
we have.

00:19:35.242 --> 00:19:36.410 position:30% line:89% align:start
Pay attention.

00:19:36.443 --> 00:19:38.813 position:16% line:83% align:start
I want you to play with
the same determination

00:19:38.846 --> 00:19:40.213 position:19% line:89% align:start
and surely we'll win.

00:19:40.247 --> 00:19:41.015 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

00:19:41.049 --> 00:19:42.215 position:38% line:89% align:start
[sighs]

00:19:42.249 --> 00:19:44.451 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Shiroyama] Taro, let me
see your leg, please.

00:19:44.484 --> 00:19:45.620 position:38% line:89% align:start
[wince]

00:19:45.653 --> 00:19:48.156 position:33% line:83% align:start
It'll be best
if you don't play anymore.

00:19:48.188 --> 00:19:49.757 position:21% line:83% align:start
I don't want to risk
your health.

00:19:49.791 --> 00:19:51.092 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Mr. Misaki]
Son, how are you feeling?

00:19:51.125 --> 00:19:52.325 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-Huh?

00:19:52.860 --> 00:19:54.028 position:41% line:83% align:start
[Taro]
Dad...

00:19:54.062 --> 00:19:55.830 position:35% line:83% align:start
Tell me,
can you keep playing?

00:19:55.863 --> 00:19:56.664 position:24% line:89% align:start
If it hurts a lot,

00:19:56.698 --> 00:19:59.100 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'd rather you rest
in the bench.

00:19:59.133 --> 00:20:00.001 position:27% line:89% align:start
I'm doing fine.

00:20:00.034 --> 00:20:01.301 position:24% line:89% align:start
I can keep playing.

00:20:01.334 --> 00:20:02.503 position:24% line:89% align:start
Dad, listen to me.

00:20:02.537 --> 00:20:04.438 position:24% line:83% align:start
You'd never leave
one of your paintings

00:20:04.471 --> 00:20:06.306 position:19% line:89% align:start
half way done, right?

00:20:06.339 --> 00:20:07.508 position:30% line:89% align:start
It's the same.

00:20:07.542 --> 00:20:09.510 position:30% line:83% align:start
I don't plan on
abandoning my team.

00:20:09.544 --> 00:20:11.278 position:10% line:89% align:start
This means the world to me.

00:20:11.311 --> 00:20:12.647 position:30% line:89% align:start
I understand.

00:20:13.614 --> 00:20:14.515 position:35% line:89% align:start
[grunting]

00:20:14.549 --> 00:20:16.483 position:33% line:83% align:start
[Mr. Mikami]
 <i>I'll take care of his leg.</i>

00:20:16.517 --> 00:20:17.250 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:20:17.284 --> 00:20:18.485 position:38% line:83% align:start
[coach]
Mr. Mikami.

00:20:20.088 --> 00:20:21.122 position:13% line:89% align:start
There's no way around it.

00:20:21.155 --> 00:20:22.890 position:33% line:83% align:start
We'll have to
immobilize your leg.

00:20:22.924 --> 00:20:24.025 position:41% line:89% align:start
But...

00:20:24.058 --> 00:20:26.027 position:27% line:83% align:start
I don't plan on
stopping you this time.

00:20:26.060 --> 00:20:28.196 position:24% line:83% align:start
I want you to win
the finals.

00:20:28.228 --> 00:20:29.396 position:41% line:89% align:start
Yeah.

00:20:30.430 --> 00:20:32.399 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Roberto] Before,
when I'd get injured,

00:20:32.432 --> 00:20:34.135 position:16% line:83% align:start
my manager would give me
this massage

00:20:34.168 --> 00:20:35.536 position:24% line:89% align:start
to ease the pain.

00:20:35.570 --> 00:20:38.740 position:13% line:83% align:start
By the way, that last shot
you just made...

00:20:38.773 --> 00:20:39.674 position:24% line:89% align:start
left me awestruck.

00:20:39.707 --> 00:20:41.374 position:19% line:83% align:start
It was just a reflex,
wasn't it?

00:20:42.043 --> 00:20:43.044 position:44% line:89% align:start
Mhm.

00:20:43.077 --> 00:20:44.411 position:19% line:83% align:start
The good thing is that
your injury

00:20:44.444 --> 00:20:46.814 position:24% line:83% align:start
isn't as serious
as everyone's else's.

00:20:46.848 --> 00:20:48.015 position:24% line:89% align:start
And don't forget...

00:20:48.049 --> 00:20:49.316 position:13% line:89% align:start
that now you have to win.

00:20:49.349 --> 00:20:51.418 position:10% line:83% align:start
I'm sure we're going to win,
Roberto.

00:20:51.451 --> 00:20:53.521 position:10% line:89% align:start
I'm feeling very motivated.

00:20:53.554 --> 00:20:55.255 position:19% line:83% align:start
I'm gonna go with you
to Brazil.

00:20:56.824 --> 00:20:57.859 position:16% line:89% align:start
Okay, follow it through.

00:20:58.760 --> 00:21:01.162 position:13% line:83% align:start
For now, just concentrate
on winning.

00:21:01.195 --> 00:21:03.898 position:33% line:83% align:start
That's what's
most important now.

00:21:03.931 --> 00:21:04.699 position:41% line:89% align:start
Yeah!

00:21:05.066 --> 00:21:06.167 position:35% line:89% align:start
[cheers]

00:21:06.200 --> 00:21:07.034 position:10% line:83% align:start
[announcer] The temperature
 <i>is rising,</i>

00:21:07.068 --> 00:21:08.268 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>ladies and gentlemen.</i>

00:21:08.301 --> 00:21:10.437 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>And these young players</i>
 <i>will have to play</i>

00:21:10.470 --> 00:21:12.840 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>under an overwhelming</i>
 <i>heat.</i>

00:21:12.874 --> 00:21:13.775 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>Now, the extra time</i>

00:21:13.808 --> 00:21:15.342 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>for Nankatsu</i>
 <i>and Meiwa's match</i>

00:21:15.375 --> 00:21:16.811 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>is about to begin.</i>

00:21:17.945 --> 00:21:19.781 position:19% line:89% align:start
You can do it, honey.

00:21:19.814 --> 00:21:20.948 position:24% line:89% align:start
Son, you got this.

00:21:20.982 --> 00:21:22.784 position:10% line:89% align:start
You can do it, Big Brother.

00:21:22.817 --> 00:21:23.818 position:33% line:89% align:start
 <i>This time,</i>

00:21:23.851 --> 00:21:27.188 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>I won't let victory</i>
 <i>slip through my fingers.</i>

00:21:27.221 --> 00:21:28.990 position:35% line:83% align:start
[Tsubasa]
 <i>We won't lose to Meiwa.</i>

00:21:29.023 --> 00:21:30.958 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>We will be the champions.</i>

00:21:30.992 --> 00:21:32.260 position:16% line:89% align:start
You can do it, Nankatsu.

00:21:32.292 --> 00:21:33.728 position:19% line:83% align:start
[announcer] Everything
comes down to

00:21:33.761 --> 00:21:34.862 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>these ten minutes.</i>

00:21:34.896 --> 00:21:35.730 position:30% line:89% align:start
 <i>And Team Meiwa</i>

00:21:35.763 --> 00:21:37.031 position:16% line:83% align:start
- <i>starts with the ball.</i>
-[whistle]

00:21:38.800 --> 00:21:40.201 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>The extra time starts,</i>
 <i>and of course,</i>

00:21:40.234 --> 00:21:41.969 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>Hyuga the Tiger is</i>
 <i>leading the pack.</i>

00:21:42.003 --> 00:21:43.070 position:30% line:89% align:start
Come on, guys.

00:21:43.104 --> 00:21:44.872 position:19% line:83% align:start
We gotta take the ball
away from him.

00:21:44.906 --> 00:21:46.908 position:13% line:83% align:start
[announcer] Team Nankatsu
doesn't waste any time.

00:21:46.941 --> 00:21:49.210 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>They're getting closer</i>
 <i>to steal the ball.</i>

00:21:49.243 --> 00:21:50.945 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>Hyuga passes it</i>
 <i>to Sawada.</i>

00:21:50.978 --> 00:21:51.946 position:41% line:89% align:start
Here.

00:21:51.979 --> 00:21:54.048 position:10% line:83% align:start
[announcer] Sawada passes it
 <i>back to Hyuga.</i>

00:21:54.081 --> 00:21:56.818 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>Meiwa's captain used to</i>
 <i>play as if he were alone,</i>

00:21:56.851 --> 00:22:00.221 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>but now, he's playing</i>
 <i>with excellent teamwork.</i>

00:22:00.254 --> 00:22:01.589 position:35% line:89% align:start
Kojiro...

00:22:01.622 --> 00:22:03.558 position:35% line:89% align:start
[panting]

00:22:03.591 --> 00:22:04.892 position:35% line:83% align:start
[Kojiro]
 <i>Now that he's injured,</i>

00:22:04.926 --> 00:22:07.128 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>I'll be able to score</i>
 <i>on him easily.</i>

00:22:07.161 --> 00:22:08.229 position:44% line:83% align:start
-No!
-No!

00:22:08.262 --> 00:22:09.630 position:27% line:77% align:start
-[grunt]
-[announcer]
Hyuga stops.

00:22:09.664 --> 00:22:11.899 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>Looks like he'll try to</i>
 <i>make it from that distance.</i>

00:22:11.933 --> 00:22:13.167 position:24% line:89% align:start
Try and block this.

00:22:13.201 --> 00:22:15.303 position:7% line:83% align:start
[announcer] It's a shot from
outside the penalty area.

00:22:15.335 --> 00:22:16.938 position:19% line:89% align:start
Stop him, Wakabayashi.

00:22:16.971 --> 00:22:18.573 position:5% line:83% align:start
[announcer] The star goalkeeper
is injured.

00:22:18.606 --> 00:22:20.741 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>Will he be able to</i>
 <i>stop the shot?</i>

00:22:20.775 --> 00:22:23.044 position:35% line:89% align:start
[grunting]

00:22:23.077 --> 00:22:24.278 position:30% line:83% align:start
[announcer]
 <i>He... He's got it!</i>

00:22:24.312 --> 00:22:26.280 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>Genzo Wakabayashi</i>
 <i>stops the ball.</i>

00:22:26.314 --> 00:22:27.281 position:44% line:89% align:start
No!

00:22:27.315 --> 00:22:28.448 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:22:28.481 --> 00:22:30.751 position:33% line:83% align:start
Wakabayashi,
what a great save!

00:22:30.785 --> 00:22:31.652 position:38% line:89% align:start
 <i>Hyuga...</i>

00:22:31.686 --> 00:22:33.453 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>Even if I have to</i>
 <i>break my leg,</i>

00:22:33.486 --> 00:22:36.624 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>you won't score on me</i>
 <i>and we won't lose to you.</i>

